Subject: [PATCH] test: stress + invariant guards for native packer and MCP
 server

- test_native_invariants.py: placement bounds, no same-layer overlap,
  determinism, height budget, empty/single/oversized edge cases, and the
  Python-fallback path when the compiled module is absent. Asserts validity,
  not bit-identity (native is an opt-in heuristic).
- test_mcp_server.py: JSON-RPC handshake, tool schema stability, unknown
  method/tool errors, messy/empty/garbage CSV ingestion, ingest->optimize
  pipeline, and a real stdio subprocess roundtrip incl. malformed-JSON survival.
100 tests pass; parity and existing suite unchanged.
